description: From Latin sexāgēnārius (“containing 60”) + -an (“forming adjectives and representative nouns”), either directly or via French sexagénaire, from Latin sexāgēnī (“60 each”) + -ārius (“-ary”), from sexāgintā (“six tens, 60”).

examples: Coordinate terms: vicenarian, tricenarian, quadragenarian, quinquagenarian, semicentenarian, septuagenarian, nonagenarian, centenarian, supercentenarian

entries.meaning: Synonym of sixtysomething: a person between 60 and 69 years old.
